Defendant will comply with all federal, and state laws, and local alcohol, drug and violence ordinances during the period of this Agreement.  If there is a case charging a violation of a criminal statute or local ordinance pending when this agreement is due to expire, this agreement continues in effect until 30 days after such case is revolved.  If the Defendant is charged with a criminal offense in a case subsequent to the Court's approval of this agreement, a finding of probable cause in that case is sufficient basis for termination of this agreement.  Defendant will keep Douglas County Clerk of Courts informed of his address and telephone number at all times, and stipulates that the sending of notice by regular mail to the address on file with the Clerk of Courts constitutes sufficient notice of any court hearings scheduled in this matter.  The non-appearance of the defendant may result in the issuance of an arrest warrant.
Defendant will pay a fine of $50 plus the costs of this action as determined by the Clerk of Courts no later than May 15, 2022.
  Defendant will continue to comply with all bail or bond conditions ordered by the Court while this agreement is in effect.

Defendant will undergo an evaluation no later than June 1, 2022 and will sign a release of information to allow the service provider to communicate with the District Attorney's Office. Defendant will provide a copy of the AODA evaluation to the District Attorney's Office within thirty (30) days of completion of the evaluation. Defendant will follow all recommendations made by said evaluation and will provide documentation showing completion/continued efforts to comply with said recommendations between 30 and 60 days prior to the end of this agreement.
Defendant will be truthful and accurate with the assessor and will inform the assessor of the current charge in this case and any drug or alcohol related charges in other pending or resolved cases.
If Defendant makes a good faith effort to schedule an evaluation to occur before the date above, but is not able to complete the evaluation by that date, the date for completion of the evaluation may be extended by agreement of the parties upon reasonable notice to the District Attorney's Office. Failure to notify the State of hardship in completing the evaluation prior to the date agreed upon constitutes evidence that Defendant did not make a good faith effort to schedule and complete said evaluation.

Court recites charges against defendant and possible penalties.  Defendant advised of right to consult an attorney. Defendant pleads not guilty. States request on bail: $250 cash bond with conditions of no contact with victim 1 as outlined in the ID Key, no use of alcohol, do not return to 702 Tower Ave., Centerfolds. State indicates that defendant does not have any criminal history in the State of Wisconsin. Defendant has history entirely in Minnesota and all traffic. In every case in Minnesota, defendant failed to appear in those traffic cases and they ended up being defaulted. State states she doesn't have local ties. Defendant does not object to State's request.
